---
import BlogLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';

const title = "How Often Should You Restripe a Commercial Parking Lot?";
const description = "Expert guidance on parking lot restriping frequency in Missouri. Learn the 18-24 month rule, signs your lot needs attention, and why waiting costs more.";
const publishDate = "June 23, 2026";
---

<BlogLayout {title} {description} {publishDate}>
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary-dark">How Often Should You Restripe a Commercial Parking Lot?</h1>
  
  <img src="/images/xai_grok-imagine-image_20260623_180927_63d294da.jpg" alt="Fresh parking lot striping" class="rounded-2xl my-10 w-full shadow-2xl" />
  
  <p>The standard recommendation for Missouri commercial parking lots is to restripe every <strong>18–24 months</strong>. UV exposure, freeze-thaw cycles, and heavy traffic in Greene County accelerate fading.</p>
  
  <h2>Signs Your Lot Needs Restriping Now</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Faded or invisible stall lines</li>
    <li>Customer complaints about parking disputes</li>
    <li>ADA symbols are no longer clearly visible</li>
    <li>Insurance inspector flags</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p class="mt-12 font-medium text-brand-yellow">Schedule a free lot assessment in Springfield today.</p>
</BlogLayout>
